cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a graph problem, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of LP rounding and primal-dual algorithms suggests it could be in cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The problem itself involves finding a connected subgraph, which could place it in cs.CG (computational geometry). The focus on approximation algorithms and analysis suggests it could be in cs.GT (computational complexity and cryptography) or cs.CC (computational complexity).
